During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Sarah Sanders discussed the meeting between President Trump and the Emir of Qatar, highlighting their discussions on security, economic issues, and efforts to combat terrorism financing. Sanders also mentioned that President Trump spoke with British Prime Minister Theresa May and both leaders condemned Syrian President Assad's use of chemical weapons. As a result, President Trump decided not to attend the Summit of the Americas in Colombia and instead Vice President Pence will attend on his behalf. The briefing also touched on topics such as the raid on Michael Cohen's office, the President's power to fire Special Counsel Robert Mueller, and the ongoing investigation into Russian meddling in the 2016 election. Sanders emphasized that the President believes the investigation is a witch hunt and that his focus is on important issues like Syria, North Korea, and tax cuts. The briefing concluded with questions about personnel changes and trade relations with China.